the aliens of the deep sea.

00:01:03.935 --> 00:01:07.152 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:07.152 --> 00:01:23.420 align:middle line:90%


00:01:23.420 --> 00:01:26.800 align:middle line:84%
The octopus has long
inspired fear and loathing.

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:30.350 align:middle line:84%
A slimy creature hurtling up
from the bottom of the sea

00:01:30.350 --> 00:01:34.740 align:middle line:84%
to attack ships and drag
unlucky sailors to their deaths

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:35.710 align:middle line:90%
in the dark sea.

00:01:35.710 --> 00:01:40.280 align:middle line:90%


00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:42.100 align:middle line:84%
But is there any
truth to the myth?

00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:48.340 align:middle line:90%


00:01:48.340 --> 00:01:54.000 align:middle line:10%
The Finisterrae Aquarium in La
Coruna in Northwestern Spain.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:58.100 align:middle line:10%
Antonio Cribeiro is the
aquarium's head biologist.

00:01:58.100 --> 00:02:01.450 align:middle line:84%
He's been studying the behavior
and intelligence of the octopus

00:02:01.450 --> 00:02:02.690 align:middle line:90%
for the last 10 years.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:08.025 align:middle line:90%


00:02:08.025 --> 00:02:10.150 align:middle line:84%
But what most
people don't know is

00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:12.620 align:middle line:84%
that while we've been
studying the octopus,

00:02:12.620 --> 00:02:15.290 align:middle line:84%
the octopus has
been studying us.

00:02:15.290 --> 00:02:21.010 align:middle line:90%


00:02:21.010 --> 00:02:23.010 align:middle line:84%
This dimension of
octopus behavior

00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:25.580 align:middle line:90%
doesn't really surprise Antonio.

00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:28.720 align:middle line:84%
In fact, those who work
with octopuses in aquariums

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.980 align:middle line:84%
have their work cut
out for them just

00:02:30.980 --> 00:02:34.340 align:middle line:90%
keeping them in their tanks.

00:02:34.340 --> 00:02:37.970 align:middle line:84%
Turn your back, and an octopus
can crawl out of one tank

00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:40.630 align:middle line:84%
and slip into another
to get its prey,

00:02:40.630 --> 00:02:42.730 align:middle line:90%
and then quietly return home.

00:02:42.730 --> 00:02:45.690 align:middle line:90%


00:02:45.690 --> 00:02:48.580 align:middle line:84%
So just who is this
curious creature

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:51.490 align:middle line:84%
who leaves the comfort
of its watery world

00:02:51.490 --> 00:02:54.660 align:middle line:84%
and seems as interested
in us as we are in it?

00:02:54.660 --> 00:03:05.660 align:middle line:90%


00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:08.580 align:middle line:84%
Antonio knows this isn't
an animal who simply

00:03:08.580 --> 00:03:10.560 align:middle line:90%
made a break for freedom.

00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:14.095 align:middle line:84%
This is an intelligent creature
who's mapping its environment.

00:03:14.095 --> 00:03:17.240 align:middle line:90%


00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:19.525 align:middle line:84%
But just how intelligent
is the octopus?

00:03:19.525 --> 00:03:23.450 align:middle line:90%


00:03:23.450 --> 00:03:27.700 align:middle line:84%
Antonio is going to make little
Pepino undergo a slew of tests.

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:29.580 align:middle line:84%
This time there
will be no escape.

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:33.017 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:33.017 --> 00:03:49.740 align:middle line:90%


00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:51.540 align:middle line:84%
Most animals learn
the skills they

00:03:51.540 --> 00:03:54.040 align:middle line:84%
need from their
parents to find food

00:03:54.040 --> 00:03:55.940 align:middle line:90%
and to hide from their enemies.

00:03:55.940 --> 00:03:58.600 align:middle line:90%
Much of the rest is instinctual.

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:00.820 align:middle line:84%
The sign of true
intelligence is when

00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:03.650 align:middle line:84%
