agile as human hands

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:45.190 align:middle line:84%
as they explore the novelty
of the screw top jar.

00:04:45.190 --> 00:04:47.190 align:middle line:84%
Here, it seems,
the octopus is not

00:04:47.190 --> 00:04:49.910 align:middle line:84%
using instinct but
cognitive reasoning to solve

00:04:49.910 --> 00:04:53.190 align:middle line:84%
this problem, thinking
if the crab got in there,

00:04:53.190 --> 00:04:55.370 align:middle line:84%
there must be a
way to get it out.

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:58.765 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:12.000 align:middle line:90%


00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.546 align:middle line:84%
Pepino thinks through the
problem until he succeeds.

00:05:15.546 --> 00:05:18.785 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:18.785 --> 00:05:35.440 align:middle line:90%


00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:38.400 align:middle line:84%
The hardest part is to believe
that this animal is simply

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:39.230 align:middle line:90%
a mollusk.

00:05:39.230 --> 00:05:42.320 align:middle line:84%
